<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="280" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[106,204,1567,1591]" box="[106,204,1567,1591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[106,204,1567,1591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="280">Remarks:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[106,1096,1605,1659]" pageId="13" pageNumber="280">
This is the only known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[456,532,1605,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aulacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,532,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="280">Aulacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this region to have both the antenna and ovipositor sheath with a central white band.
</paragraph>
